Bangladesh current caretaker government is striving to take steps, welcoming help from home and abroad, to fight against the current flooding catastrophe while the situation likely worsens in central region including capital Dhaka.
Hundreds of thousands of villagers fled their homes Monday as flash floods caused by monsoon rains and glacial snowmelt inundated large swathes of northern Bangladesh ,.
Six more people were drowned in floodwaters in two districts in Bangladesh ,.
